  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p>\r\n<p>Cut the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Add them to a pot of <strong>water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once boiling, cook for 15 min or until fork-tender&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/432_step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/432_step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/432_step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/432_step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/432_step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and dice the<strong> red onion<span style=\"color: #e86754;\">[s]</span>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Peel and dice the <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Tip: this is best done by quartering the carrots lengthways and then cutting across</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/432_step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/432_step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/432_step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/432_step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/432_step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of&nbsp;<strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced&nbsp;carrot</strong>,<strong> diced&nbsp;onion</strong> and <strong>dried&nbsp;</strong><strong>bay leaf<span class=\"text-danger\">[ves]</span></strong>&nbsp;with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cook for 5 min, or until softened and starting to colour &ndash; this is your<strong> carrot mixture</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/432_step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/432_step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/432_step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/432_step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/432_step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve the <strong>beef&nbsp;</strong><strong>stock cube</strong><span style=\"color: #e86754;\"><strong>[s]</strong>&nbsp;</span>in 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span>&nbsp;<strong>boiled water</strong></p>\r\n<p>Grate the <strong>cheddar</strong></p>\r\n<p>Trim and chop the <strong>spring onion<span style=\"color: #e86754;\">[s]</span></strong>&nbsp;finely</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/432_step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/432_step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/432_step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/432_step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/432_step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>beef mince</strong> and <strong>chopped&nbsp;garlic</strong> to the <strong>carrot mixture</strong> and increase the heat to high</p>\r\n<p>Cook for 5 min further, or until the mince has browned, breaking it up as you go</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
